                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13916390" author="jahewson" created="Fri, 28 Feb 2014 21:10:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looks like a problem with stroking + filling combined and/or line width. I&apos;ll take a look soon.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13943954" author="tilman" created="Sat, 22 Mar 2014 07:00:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I took a look at the &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-1870&quot; title=&quot;PDFunctionType0 incorrect&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-1870&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-1870&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; file. The final image is really made of six triangles, and then a hexagone shape is drawn in the middle. The line of the hexagone is white, and its surface is black. So it is the white line that is too small.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Both the pre-regression version and the current version have an identity CTM. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;del&gt;The difference between the two versions is that the java graphics has an scale of 1, while the current one has a scale of 4.16 (the number for 300dpi).&lt;/del&gt; true but irrelevant, solution coming up&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1 1 1 1 1 1 scn    &amp;lt;===== black&lt;br/&gt;
/Cs9 CS 0 0 0 0 0 0 SCN    &amp;lt;==== white&lt;br/&gt;
0 J 0 j 36 w 10 M []0 d       &amp;lt;===== line width is 36&lt;br/&gt;
450 396 m    &amp;lt;========== moveto&lt;br/&gt;
378 520.708 l    &amp;lt;========line&lt;br/&gt;
234 520.708 l&lt;br/&gt;
162 396 l&lt;br/&gt;
234 271.292 l&lt;br/&gt;
378 271.292 l&lt;br/&gt;
b     &amp;lt;============== Close, fill, and then stroke the path,&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13944037" author="tilman" created="Sat, 22 Mar 2014 12:24:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I solved the problem with the Vattenfall file, the cause is similar to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-1830&quot; title=&quot;Grey background rectangle rendered at different position&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-1830&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-1830&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: a wrong initialisation. Rev 1571581 had incorrectly changed the initialization of lineCap from 0 (= CAPBUTT) to CAPSQUARE. The spec tells &quot;A code specifying the shape of the endpoints for any open path that is stroked (see &#8220;Line Cap Style&#8221; on page 216). Initial value: 0, for square butt caps.&quot; I changed it back to 0 (CAPBUTT) in rev 1580201 and the vattenfall file is now OK.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13944085" author="tilman" created="Sat, 22 Mar 2014 14:16:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I solved the problem with the hexagone file. The difference between a few weeks ago and now is that previously, the path was filled (f) and then stroked (S). Currently the path is stroked and then filled. This is wrong, the spec tells &quot;fill, and then stroke the path&quot;. (It makes sense when thinking about it - both operations do overlap, so the sequence is important) In a first step, I fixed strokeAndFillPath() in rev 1580212. I then renamed the methods in rev 1580214.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13944180" author="jahewson" created="Sat, 22 Mar 2014 18:55:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yep, the initial stroke should be CAP_BUTT and strokeAndFillPath is indeed backwards, thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
